description: {"blocks":[{"key":"3vhdv","text":"The goal of this study is to map the pudendal nerve with imaging and electrophysiology by gathering additional data from patients receiving an implanted neurostimulator as part of their normal clinical care, and to examine the response of the bladder and urethra to different pudendal nerve stimulation frequencies in humans. There are 5 main parts to this study. Participants complete pre and post study questionnaires to asses their pelvic health and functional change. Volumetric imaging with MRI and CT scans are done to create patient specific maps of each participant's pelvic anatomy. Additional details on the parameters used for the MRI and CT scans can be found here:dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.yxmvm978bl3p/v1. During device implantation experimental trials are performed in the OR to asses the impact of different simulation parameters on the pelvic floor. After device implantation experimental trials are performed during a cystometrogram to asses how bladder state and stimulation parameters affect pelvic floor and lower urinary tract function.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":677,"length":48}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"8EDB40A1719D11F0B29F0A58A9FEAC02","url":"http://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.yxmvm978bl3p/v1"}}}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1snd","text":"After multicontact lead has been placed next to the pudendal nerve as described in Peters 2013, connect the external pulse generator to electrode 0 and a surface patch electrode placed on the ankle.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5ktmr","text":"Change pulse width to 210 microseconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"48qqi","text":"Change stimulation frequency of the external pulse generator to 3 Hz.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c5o9u","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude until external anal sphincter contraction is detected by intraoperative nueromonitoring team on EMG readout then turn off stimulation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3hl23","text":"Change pulse width to 60 microseconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9a1bq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3umr5","text":"Double previous stimulation amplitude and apply stimulation for 10 seconds. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aklnl","text":"Repeat step 9 and all substeps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5881r","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7d2c0","text":"Change pulse width to 450 microseconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5iumc","text":"Repeat step 9 and all substeps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3qa5e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cbj3r","text":"Connect to electrode 1.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8qhng","text":"Repeat steps 8-13.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8s1a6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bk909","text":"Connect to electrode 2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1p86c","text":"Repeat steps 8-13.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f46vq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"d8va5","text":"Connect to electrode 3.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"758ba","text":"Repeat steps 8-13.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"16ka1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fncj9","text":"Connect implanted lead to temporary pulse generator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bh19i","text":"Set the electrode with the lowest external anal sphincter activation threshold as the cathode and set the electrode with the second lowest external anal sphincter activation threshold as the anode.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a951u","text":"Repeat steps 8 and 9.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c859a","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5qlbf","text":"Set the electrode with the second lowest external anal sphincter activation threshold as the cathode and set the electrode with the lowest external anal sphincter activation threshold as the anode.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9nkn7","text":"Add lubricating jelly to the tip of the Manoscan catheter and place catheter into the urethra until resistance is met and catheter cannot go any deeper.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f5l5e","text":"Place electromyography (EMG) needles across the anal sphincter at the 3 and 9 o'clock position until the needle is no longer visible [7].","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ep9op","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"4fo7m","text":" Connect the needle electrodes to Cadwell Cascade Elite intraoperative neuromonitoring system and begin recording with a sampling rate of 333 Hz.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"citation","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"align":"","authors":"Peters KM","can_edit":true,"created_on":"","date":1364774400,"doi":"https://doi.org/10.1111/jsm.12138","guid":"049B6E4E88D94B7F8A0B67F86B730FC7","id":0,"journal":"","protocol_guid":"","protocol_id":0,"title":"Pudendal neuromodulation for sexual dysfunction."}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"202gr","text":"Place urodynamics TDOT air charged catheter into the urethra and rectum. Place EMG patch electrode across the anus at the 3 and 9 o'clock position. Connect sensors to Laborie urodynamics system and begin recording. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2s1gm","text":"Using the pudendal neurostimulator control software set the case as the anode and electrode 0 as the cathode. Determine the sensory threshold and maximum tolerable threshold at 14 Hz and 210 microsecond pulse width.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8ag6e","text":"Fill the bladder until participant feels a strong urge to void.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4fpe1","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude until participant first senses stimulation. Remain at this amplitude for at least ten seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eukhd","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude to participants maximum tolerable threshold. Remain at this amplitude for at least ten seconds. Then turn off stimulation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"enr20","text":"Change stimulation frequency to 30 Hz.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"pfoc","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude until participant first senses stimulation. Remain at this amplitude for at least ten seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cublq","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude to participants maximum tolerable threshold. Remain at this amplitude for at least ten seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"494ne","text":"Set stimulation frequency to 3 Hz, set electrode with lowest sensory threshold as the anode, and set the electrode with the second lowest sensory threshold as the cathode.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eqdqh","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude until participant first senses stimulation. Remain at this amplitude for at least ten seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4k76e","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude to participants maximum tolerable threshold. Remain at this amplitude for at least ten seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8mmhc","text":"Change stimulation frequency to 30 Hz.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cjahs","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude until participant first senses stimulation. Remain at this amplitude for at least ten seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1865d","text":"Increase stimulation amplitude to participants maximum tolerable threshold. Remain at this amplitude for at least ten seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"77p7e","text":"Change electrode combination to match what the participant uses for at home therapy. {"blocks":[{"key":"992up","text":"Complete CT imaging of the pelvis after implantation of the device lead to that the lead location can be co-localized into a participants specific model of their pelvic anatomy.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1kvic","text":"Have participants complete the same surveys that were issued in step 1.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2kfra","text":"Turn on Manoscan recording software and calibrate Manoscan high-resolution esophageal small diameter catheter per Manoscan manual guidelines. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9309p","text":"Set up as described in steps 3 and 4.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8aj1e","text":"End of session. Save data from Manoscan and shut down software. Remove remaining catheters from the participant. Collect pressure and EMG data from the urodynamics system.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eotmj","text":"Record the first visible sensor outside the body using the numbered label on the catheter.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b7702","text":"Tape the catheter to the patients body so that it remains in place and does not change position or slide out.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"catgo","text":"Begin data recording session and change display so only channels in the bladder, bladder neck, and urethra are visible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
